{"lemma": "تَمِيمَةٌ", "slug": "تَمِيمَةٌ", "root": "ت.م.م", "root_slug": "ت-م-م", "root_link": "/words/roots/ت-م-م", "pos": "N", "pos_camel": "noun", "paradigm": [], "frequency_in_corpus": 0, "cross_references": {"qac": {"found": false}, "wiktextract": {"found": true, "entry_count": 1, "pos_tags": ["noun"], "has_etymology": false, "sense_count": 1}, "lanes": {"found": true, "entry_ids": ["n4097"], "search_url": "https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%AA%D9%8E%D9%85%D9%90%D9%8A%D9%85%D9%8E%D8%A9%D9%8C"}}, "translations": {"en": "amulet", "fa": "تعویذ", "ur": "تعویذ", "tr": "büyü boncuğu", "id": "jimat", "bn": "তালি", "es": "amuleto", "fr": "amulette", "de": "Amulett", "ru": "талисман", "zh": "护身符"}, "definition": {"source": "wiktextract", "senses": [{"pos": "noun", "gloss": "talisman, amulet"}]}, "etymology": null, "ipa": ["/ta.miː.ma/"], "lanes_definition": {"source": "lanes", "entries": [{"entry_id": "n4097", "headword_ar": "تَمِيمَةٌ", "root": "tm", "body": [{"kind": "italic_en", "text": "A kind of amulet"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "("}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Euw*apN", "text_ar": "عُوذَةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", T, S)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "which is hung upon a human being;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "forbidden to be worn: (S:) or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "a kind of bead:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S, Mgh:) erroneously imagined by some to be the same as"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "maEaA*apN", "text_ar": "مَعَاذَةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": (El- Kutabee, Mgh:) but as to the"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "maEaA*aAt", "text_ar": "مَعَاذَات"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "that are inscribed with something from the Kur-án, or with the names of God, in these there is no harm: (S, Mgh:)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "a speckled bead, black speckled with white,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "the reverse, which is strung upon a thong, and tied to the neck:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(M, K:) sing. of"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "tamaAy^imu", "text_ar": "تَمَايِمُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and [n. un. of] ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "tamiymN", "text_ar": "تَمِيمٌ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": (T, M, K:)"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "tamaAy^imu", "text_ar": "تَمَايِمُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "signifies"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "certain beads which the Arabs of the desert used to hang upon their children, to repel, as they asserted, the evil eye:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(T, Mgh:) or the"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "tamiymap", "text_ar": "تَمِيمَة"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "is, accord. to some,"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "a necklace"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "("}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "qilaAdap", "text_ar": "قِلَادَة"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ")"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "upon which are put thongs and amulets"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "("}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Euwa*", "text_ar": "عُوَذ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "): (M:) or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "a necklace"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "("}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "qilaAdap", "text_ar": "قِلَادَة"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ")"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "of thongs:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and is sometimes applied to the"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "amulet"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "("}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Euw*ap", "text_ar": "عُوذَة"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ")"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "that is hung upon the necks of children:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(T:) but he who makes"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "tmAy^m", "text_ar": "تمايم"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "to signify"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "thongs"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "is in error: El-Farezdak uses the phrase"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "suyuwru Alt~amaAy^imi", "text_ar": "سُيُورُ التَّمَايِمِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "because they are"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "beads which are perforated, and into which are inserted thongs or strings whereby they are suspended:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(T, Mgh:) Az says, I have not found among the Arabs of the desert any difference of opinion respecting the"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "tmymp", "text_ar": "تميمة"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", as to its being the bead itself: (TA:) but accord. to En-Nakha'ee, the Prophet disapproved of everything hung upon a child or grown person, and said that all such things were"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "tmAy^m", "text_ar": "تمايم"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": (Mgh:) the"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "tmymp", "text_ar": "تميمة"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "is [said to be] thus called because by it the condition of the child is rendered complete. (Har p. 22.)"}], "source_refs": ["S", "Mgh", "M", "K", "T", "TA"]}]}, "classical_definitions": null, "translations_attribution": {"model": "qwen36-35b-heretic", "generated_date": "2026-05-18", "pipeline_version": "words.translation.v1.spark"}}